title: Frieze, 1905–15
description: Art nouveau/mission style. Floral wreaths with fleur-de-lis insets connected by floral swags suspended from top band of palmette-like ornaments. The bottom third has a band of large geometric medallions and rest of the background has small, staggered, modeled squares. All forms are outlined in thin beading.Tan ground covered in light grey fanning circles and irregular white dots. Printed in tans, browns and metallic gold. Printed in selvedge: "Liberty Papers"

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-581.
